The ‘32 Roadster never runs hot, but it pegged the temp gauge last night doing around 80-85mph on the express lanes (due to low coolant level in the radiator)…which scared the crap out of me and made me coast over to the shoulder.  Got this neat photo though, so it wasn’t all bad. (PS: The car cooled off and I drove it to my destination where I added about 3/4 gallon of water to the radiator.  I think it just slowly puked it all out of the overflow and catch can over the last year. I should probably check coolant level more often). #hotrod #deuceroadster #blownflathead #flathead

Some Halibrand 201 V8 quick change rear cover progression.  The polished one on the left is a 2-ear Culver City version and is the first style made as far as I know.  I was surprised to see that the inside of the cover was not cast the same as newer versions, and uses slightly smaller OD bearings.  The two in the middle have 4 ears, and are Culver City and Torrance City versions.  The far right is a new Rodsville, which is a dead ringer for the Halibrand covers except it has 3 ears.  There are at least a couple other versions also, but I believe they would be newer than the 3 Halibrand covers shown here.  #halibrand #quickchange #quickchangerearend #hotrodparts #hotrod

SOLD: NOS Schroeder steering box.  8:1 ratio. 14” from the edge of the left mounting flange to column centerline.  This is the correct size for early Ford hot rods. Has a splined coupler input, so you can make the column any length you want. It was mocked up in a car but never ran, so there are some real light marks where it was clamped in, other than that it’s in new condition. (SOLD) DM for questions or to buy.  @partswapper #partswapper @texashotrodswap #hotrodpartsforsale #hotrodparts #hotrod #schroedersteering

SOLD: Magnesium Halibrand 201 V8 quick change.  This is a rare early magnesium housing with a very early Culver City 2-ear rear cover.  It was fully polished at one time, but the magnesium has turned dark over the years, as it does.  If you want to polish it again it would be very easy to do so.  I believe that the rear cover is original to the center section.  Includes a 3.78:1 ring and pinion and a number 18 set of change gears.  Closed drive lower shaft for torque tube.  Turns pretty nice from the input, has what feels like the appropriate amount of bearing drag.  I lightly cleaned the pinion support area and I don’t see any of the typical cracks.  The outside of the housing is nice, but there are a few very minor scuffs/ patina from it being handled (see pics). In my opinion it should be ready to fit up/assemble, and run.  Not cheap, but not easy to find one like this, and I need money to buy nitro and race car parts.  DM for questions or to purchase.  #hotrodparts #magnesium #halibrand #quickchange #halibrandquickchange #hotrodpartsforsale #partswapper @partswapper @texashotrodswap

A tip on assembling a 1939 Ford transmission.  If you can’t get the input installed because it’s hitting the cluster gear…stop.  Remove the rear bearing from the output shaft.  Then assemble further.  If you grind on the input, that will evidently make it weak, because that’s where this one broke two teeth off of the main drive gear.  #hotrodparts #flathead #earlyford #transmission #hotrod #protips #1939transmission

“Herda” scoop I made for the race car out of 304 stainless steel.  The idea behind the scoop is to distribute the air evenly to/through the injector with the turning vanes. This keeps air from “stacking up” and the rear of the scoop.  The inlet at the front is sized with an equation that takes into account how much air the engine can use at a given mph and rpm.  This one is actually oversized for the half Donovan 4-banger, but should be right for the V8 going in the car next.  #hotrod #herdascoop #bonnevilleroadster #nitromethane #donovanhemi #bonnevillesaltflats #scta #racecar #hotrod #basskustom

Today’s my birthday (thanks y’all!), and I was really hoping that I would be able to fire up the race car.  But, checking valve to piston clearance after installing new head studs revealed that I did not have enough clearance on the intake valve…even with a thicker head gasket.  My friend (and 200mph Bonneville roadster guy) Ed Stuck came over and we degreed the (huge) cam again just to be sure.  So next I’m going to fly-cut the valve notches on the pistons and then bolt it all back together (hopefully soon) so I can finally fire it up in preparation for running at Speedweek. #hotrod #donovanhemi #nitro #bonnevilleroadster #bonnevillesaltflats #twostepsforward #onestepback

Fly-cutting forged Arias Hemi pistons on a shop-made fixture to increase piston to valve clearance.  Shooting for .060” clearance with a thicker head gasket (and nailed it). I’m not a machinist…but I’ve played one on TV.  #manualmachinist #hotrod #donovanhemi #nitromethane #hemi #basskustom

I first met Peter Vincent at Bonneville 20 years ago, in 2003.  I knew who he was from seeing his photography in various magazines, and I was very surprised when he wanted to shoot my primered Shoebox Ford for one of his books.  I kept in touch with him through the years and I always appreciated his outlook on hot rodding.  I knew him as an easy-going Idaho hippie of sorts, and as a very talented photographer who took his craft seriously.  In this photo, he was shooting my Model A Coupe (which eventually ended up as a feature in Rod N Custom). RIP Peter.  #petervincent #bonnevillesaltflats #hotrod #hotrodphotography

Race car update: I hadn’t been real happy with the Donovan 417 block we were going to use as a 4-banger in the roadster…so when the opportunity arose to switch to a Emery/ Rodeck billet 392 block, I decided that I needed to make it happen.  The car is ready to fire up now…should make some noise with it by the end of this week.  Bonneville Speedweek is only a month away. #bonneville #bonnevillesaltflats #hotrod #unblownfuelroadster #nitrohemi #392hemi #nitromethane #scta

Yesterday was a long day.  We did get the roadster fired up on alcohol (and it sounds bitchin’ on alcohol), but we discovered that I had a leak from a couple pinholes that I missed in the fuel tank.  So we had to abort the plan to switch the car over to nitro.  I’ll get the tanks checked out and weld up the pinholes, and hopefully we can run it on nitro sometime next week. (I just had to share that rear 3/4 angle pic though.) In the wise words of Paula Abdul…”two steps forward, one step back.” #hotrod #bonnevillesaltflats #bonnevilleroadster #unblownfuelroadster #nitro #scta #basskustom

Fired the roadster on nitro for the first time today. It's running on methanol (and not very well honestly) until the very end of the video when it's starting the switch to nitro. We shut it off right after because we needed to do some fiddling with the air gap on the injector butterflies to get the idle down a bit...and then the freshly rebuilt RCD crank-mount starter broke. Shit. I'm sending this one back to RCD, and I'm going to try to borrow a starter from Pete (on the left in the video) to hopefully fire the car again over the weekend. Thanks to Ed, Pete, Dean and Noah @meaneyedcat_noah (director of photography) for the help today. It's an uphill battle but we're gonna get it sorted out. #hotrod #hotrodding #scta #bonnevillesaltflats #unblownfuelroadster #nitromethane #basskustom

We have ourselves a race car! Fired the car on nitro again today after Ed, Pete, and myself sorted out a few issues and made some adjustments.  It had 80% in the tank today and it sounded absolutely bitchin’. It was so cool sitting in the drivers seat and having that little Hemi cackling and making my eyes water…after spending the last decade planning to build this car, and the last year and a half building it from essentially nothing.  Now I just need to paint the numbers and letters on it and tie up a couple loose ends, and it’s ready to load in the trailer for Speedweek. #chefskiss #hotrod #scta #nitrohemi #unblownfuelroadster #bonnevillesaltflats #bonneville #speedweek
It’s ready.  Roadster is in the box and ready to go to Speedweek at the Bonneville Salt Flats.  See y’all there.  @sctabniofficial #bonnevillesaltflats #speedweek #unblownfuelroadster #basskustom

We made it to Wendover yesterday evening.  The salt got rain on Tuesday night, and we are waiting for it to dry out.  So today we got the car out and made sure the belts were adjusted to fit me, and fixed a fuel shut-off that was binding up. (Also thanks to Lee Kennedy for coming and giving the car a pre-inspection this morning). We are going to try to get the car inspected in the morning at the airport, and we are then going to be in a holding pattern until the salt dries up.  Right now the general consensus seems to be racing on Monday or Tuesday.  #bonnevillespeedweek #unblownfuelroadster #hotrod

social_posts.post_text: In line to make the rookie run.  Cross your fingers for us that we know what we are doing and don’t look like assholes. #bonnevillesaltflats #bonnevillespeedweek #hotrod #unblownfuelroadster

Made the first rookie run today, and learned A LOT. (TLDR: Car seems good, driver needs work) So I’ve been coming out here to Bonneville for 20 years, and have crewed on Ed’s roadster for around 15 of those, but I’d never driven a race car here.  And…this is a brand new car that I had never driven anywhere until today, and it had 90% nitro in it.  But the car did great.  Nothing fell off, engine stayed together, had consistent oil pressure, made good power, EGTs looked good, clutch, transmission and driveline worked perfect.  I could steer it and it seemed to go relatively straight (for a roadster)…or at least I didn’t run into anything.  I got up to 131 mph going through the 2 (which would have been good enough to license up had I stayed in it until the 3 mile). But I pulled off early and didn’t get all the way off the track, which got me in a little hot water.  The good news is that now I know a lot more about the car and the course, and I’m pretty sure I’ll do a lot better on the next pass.  We added some timing, put some more fuel in the tank, and we’ll try it again tomorrow.  #bonnevillespeedweek #bonnevillesaltflats #hotrod #unblownfuelroadster #rookiedrivernomore

Just made a licensing pass, went 150 mph at the 3 mile for a 139 mph average between the 2 and the 3…so that is good enough for my D competition license.  Car has A LOT more in it.  I barely got into the throttle, and when I did finally get the pedal down it fuckin’ trucked.  The guys on my team said that the little 4-banger was cackling pretty good at the line.  Next up will hopefully be a 175 mph licensing pass.  #bonnevillesaltflats #scta #bonnevillespeedweek #hotrod #unblownfuelroadster #noproblemo

Well that’s it for Speedweek 2023…and I think we made the best of what we had to work with.  I got to make three runs in the car, and learned more about the car and the track each time.  The fastest I got it up to (so far) was 151 mph, and I expected to go faster than that today…but we changed the main bypass jet yesterday after looking at the Racepak, when we should have just left it alone.  I drove the car a lot better today but we just missed the tune-up.  I have to say that I’m plenty pleased with how well the car drives, and I’m looking forward to going much faster in it next time. (Thanks to dkphoto for the great rolling shot). #bonnevillespeedweek #bonnevillesaltflats #hotrod #scta #nitro #hemi #unblownfuelroadster #basskustom

Made it home safe and sound with the roadster.  Still have some cleaning and maintenance ahead of me, but the car is still in one piece and I don’t think we hurt the engine at all…so that’s good.  I really need to thank all the guys that came to help me make this dream a reality. You just can’t run a nitro car by yourself, and it’s hard work…so I’m thankful that I had such a hard-working, talented, and experienced team.  Albert, George, Ed, Vince, Vern, Pete Prentice, Pete Christesen, Larry, Dan, John, Donnie, and an extra special thanks to Noah and Christian for sticking with me through the entire thing.  It was stressful and exhausting, but I had more fun than I’ve had in a long time.  Thanks guys. #hotrodding #bonnevillespeedweek #unblownfuelroadster #injectednitro #hotrod #basskustom

Doane Spencer ‘55 Thunderbird.  This is the second one that he built (in the early ‘90s) that used a bunch of parts from his original ‘55 that he raced at Bonneville.  Went through a bit of a rabbithole reading about it, and I was really impressed by the Y-block.  It’s incredible.  Look at the tapered water manifolds to the heads…the long tube headers…and the hand hammered aluminum air cleaner.  Not sure where it is now, but Kirk F White sold it in 2013.  He said it was remarkably fast.  #doanespencer #hotrod #fabrication #yblock #thunderbird #55thunderbird
